The paper presents a machine-readable movement writing for sleight-of-hand moves with cards, which is axiomatized in SROIQ(D) Description Logic and collected formally as an Ontology of Card Sleights. This suggests a strong focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for developing and implementing the ontology. Additionally, the paper discusses design criteria for ensuring the ontology can be accessed and modified with a simple click-and-drag interface, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of ontologies for classification also suggests a potential fit with natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
